{"TopicId":224499,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"COM position for angled tailplane is incongrous with geometry","CreatedByName":"mattihase","CreatedById":73161,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-18T00:16:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"mattihase","CreatedById":73161,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-18T00:16:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.1 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003ECommnext, Microengineer, Trim Controller | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7-10870H | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RTX 3070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E for angled tailplane (Tail Connector B) is offset such that having the connector pointed to the side places its mass in the middle whereas pointing it up/down offsets its \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E to either side (demonstrated in video). This has the result of giving any craft including this tailplane the tendency to roll if it is used as intended.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExpected behaviour would be that pointing the tailplane to each side would shift the mass that way.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cvideo class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 controls=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.global.core.embeddedvideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Csource type=\u0022video/mp4\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/offsetCOMwrong.mp4.29feeb302ca3d41fa4a35b616c811471.mp4\u0022\u003E\u003Ca class=\u0022ipsAttachLink\u0022 data-fileext=\u0022mp4\u0022 data-fileid=\u00221522\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/attachment.php?id=1522\u0026amp;key=9b33c21ea9d6dbb627048bab2f98c230\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EoffsetCOMwrong.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/video\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222024-04-20T18:37:35Z\u0022 title=\u002204/20/2024 06:37  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Apr 20\u0022\u003EApril 20\u003C/time\u003E by The Space Peacock\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DibzNr","CreatedById":212219,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-04-20T18:59:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooking at the tail on its own makes this obvious, its center of mass seems to be randomly jammed into one of its corners\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/3image.png.28a6792e55b61e0377e1b4756c1f89d1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg data-fileid=\u00221523\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/3image.thumb.png.654d47250b50501a096c34481f8a2f1e.png\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 alt=\u00223image.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_04/2image.png.3d7c57d6f4debec6e60c903cbe5abe95.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsAttachLink ipsAttachLink_image\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg data-fileid=\u00221524\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2024_